<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1266,2012]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,318,1520,1544]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Membraneous CD, absence of median bulbus apophysis and uniform coloration similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wunderlich, 2011" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2011" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Macarophaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1277,1436,1520,1544]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Macarophaeus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wunderlich, J." box="[151,348,1556,1580]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="1 - 640" refId="ref1778" refString="Wunderlich, J. (2011) Extant and fossil spiders (Araneae). Beitrage zur Araneologie, 6, 1 - 640." type="journal article" year="2011">Wunderlich, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but separated from all current species of the latter genus by the bifid RTA with two large apical extensions (
<bibRefCitation author="Wunderlich, J." box="[278,468,1592,1616]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="1 - 640" refId="ref1778" refString="Wunderlich, J. (2011) Extant and fossil spiders (Araneae). Beitrage zur Araneologie, 6, 1 - 640." type="journal article" year="2011">Wunderlich 2011</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Denis, J." box="[479,607,1592,1616]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="1 - 118" refId="ref1566" refString="Denis, J. (1962) Les araignees de l'archipel de Madere (Mission du Professeur Vandel). Publicacoes do Instituto Zoologia Doutor Augusto Nobre, 79, 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="1962">Denis 1962</bibRefCitation>
). Differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Simon, 1914)" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[768,1157,1592,1616]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Poecilochroa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcata">
<emphasis box="[768,994,1592,1616]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Poecilochroa furcata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Simon, E." box="[1009,1150,1592,1616]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" refId="ref1740" refString="Simon, E. (1914) Les arachnides de France. Synopsis generale et catalogue des especes francaises de l'ordre des Araneae. Tome VI. 1 re partie. Roret, Paris, 308 pp." type="book" year="1914">Simon, 1914</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by the longer and thinner embolus, which appears to be as long as the conductor (embolus thicker and not as long as the conductor in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[1318,1421,1628,1652]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Poecilochroa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcata">
<emphasis box="[1318,1421,1628,1652]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">P. furcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), as well as the structure of the RTA with a more pointed and longer ventral extension in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[1135,1241,1664,1688]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Poecilochroa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcata">
<emphasis box="[1135,1241,1664,1688]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">P. furcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Simon, E." box="[1258,1396,1664,1688]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" refId="ref1740" refString="Simon, E. (1914) Les arachnides de France. Synopsis generale et catalogue des especes francaises de l'ordre des Araneae. Tome VI. 1 re partie. Roret, Paris, 308 pp." type="book" year="1914">Simon 1914</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Di Franco, F." pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="195 - 215" refId="ref1600" refString="Di Franco, F. (2001) Gnaphosidae (Arachnida, Araneae) della Riserva Naturale Orientata &quot; Oasi del Simeto &quot; (Catania). Naturalista Siciliano, 25, 195 - 215." type="journal article" year="2001">Di Franco 2001</bibRefCitation>
). Differs from other European species currently belonging to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Westring, 1874" authorityName="Westring" authorityYear="1874" box="[1084,1400,1700,1724]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Poecilochroa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1084,1227,1700,1724]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Poecilochroa</emphasis>
Westring, 1874
</taxonomicName>
by the long, bifid and similarly sized extensions of the apical part of the RTA. Appears to be similar, if not identical, to 
<taxonomicName authority="Fage, 1929" authorityName="Fage" authorityYear="1929" box="[151,515,1772,1797]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Poecilochroa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antineae">
<emphasis box="[151,392,1772,1796]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Poecilochroa antineae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fage, L." box="[398,515,1772,1797]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="248 - 254" refId="ref1636" refString="Fage, L. (1929) Mission saharienne Augieras-Draper 1927 - 1928. Araignees nouvelles. Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris, (2) 1, 248 - 254." type="journal article" year="1929">Fage, 1929</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fage, L." box="[529,646,1772,1796]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="248 - 254" refId="ref1636" refString="Fage, L. (1929) Mission saharienne Augieras-Draper 1927 - 1928. Araignees nouvelles. Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris, (2) 1, 248 - 254." type="journal article" year="1929">Fage 1929</bibRefCitation>
), described from 
<collectingCountry box="[830,883,1772,1796]" name="Serbia" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Mali</collectingCountry>
, which also possesses a scutum on the dorsal side of the opisthosoma. Compared with fig. 
<quantity box="[554,595,1808,1832]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Fage, L." box="[601,733,1808,1833]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="248 - 254" refId="ref1636" refString="Fage, L. (1929) Mission saharienne Augieras-Draper 1927 - 1928. Araignees nouvelles. Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris, (2) 1, 248 - 254." type="journal article" year="1929">Fage (1929)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fage" authorityYear="1929" box="[744,850,1809,1832]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Poecilochroa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antinae">
<emphasis box="[744,850,1809,1832]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">P. antinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by an embolus not entwined in a membraneous conductor from retrolateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="98" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1266,2012]" lastBlockId="1.[151,1437,151,284]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="98" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,466,1880,1904]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
Description of 
<typeStatus box="[368,466,1880,1904]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">holotype</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
: Pr, sternum and legs pale yellowish-brown. No teeth present on chelicerae. Eight eyes of about the same size in two rows, anterior eye row recurve. Scutum on dorsal side of Op, covering slightly less than half of Op in length. Op proximally with a cluster of long hairs. RTA bifid, with two long extensions (
<figureCitation box="[1181,1253,1952,1976]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1946,1970]" captionTargetBox="[158,1417,641,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-279@2.[151,1436,632,1922]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Poecilochroa loricata Kritscher, 1996, male holotype, right pedipalpus, drawing (setae omitted). a) ventral, scale bar = 0.5 mm b) retrolateral, scale bar = 0.5 mm c) retrolateral tibial apophysis from retrolateral—dorsal. RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis, E = embolus, CD = conductor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911143" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911143/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Fig 2c</figureCitation>
). E long, without apophyses, slightly curved and entwined by a membraneous CD. Distal part of CD lobe-like and apically rounded. Median apophysis of the bulbus absent. Pr length 2.45 (PT 2.65, 2.7), width 1.7 (PT 1.8, 1.85), Op length 2.9 (PT 2.75, 2.7). Leg measurements (Fe, Pt, Ti, Mt, Ta) as follows: I 1.6, 1, 1.2, 1.05, 0.65; II 1.55, 1.05, 1.1, 1.0, 0.65; III 1.4, 0.85, 0.95, 1.1, 0.7; IV 1.8, 1.05, 1.3, 1.7, 0.8. Leg formula (IV-I-II-III). Further details see 
<bibRefCitation author="Kritscher, E." box="[1064,1245,223,247]" pageId="1" pageNumber="98" pagination="117 - 156" refId="ref1703" refString="Kritscher, E. (1996) Ein Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Spinnen-Fauna der Maltesischen Inseln (Chelicerata: Araneae). Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, Serie B, 98, 117 - 156" type="journal article" year="1996">Kritscher (1996)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
