<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1970,2031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1970,1994]" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Kritscher, 1996" authorityName="Kritscher" authorityYear="1996" box="[282,670,1970,1995]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Poecilochroa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loricata">
<emphasis box="[282,504,1971,1995]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">Poecilochroa loricata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kritscher, E." box="[511,670,1970,1995]" pageId="1" pageNumber="98" pagination="117 - 156" refId="ref1703" refString="Kritscher, E. (1996) Ein Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Spinnen-Fauna der Maltesischen Inseln (Chelicerata: Araneae). Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, Serie B, 98, 117 - 156" type="journal article" year="1996">Kritscher, 1996</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, male holotype. a) habitus dorsal and separated leg I retrolateral, b) habitus ventral, c) right pedipalp retrolateral, d) right pedipalp ventral, e) retrolateral tibialapophysis, retrolateral-dorsal
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="100" pageId="2" pageNumber="99" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,608]" pageId="2" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis box="[199,319,151,175]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="99" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,312,151,175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="99">Comment</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Although Kritscher gave a very detailed description of several somatic characters, he only provided a sketch of the left pedipalp in retrolateral view (
<bibRefCitation author="Kritscher, E." box="[644,807,187,211]" pageId="2" pageNumber="99" pagination="117 - 156" refId="ref1703" refString="Kritscher, E. (1996) Ein Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Spinnen-Fauna der Maltesischen Inseln (Chelicerata: Araneae). Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, Serie B, 98, 117 - 156" type="journal article" year="1996">Kritscher 1996</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 7). However, the specimen in the vial labelled “Typus” (
<typeStatus box="[158,255,223,247]" pageId="2" pageNumber="99">holotype</typeStatus>
) contains a male from which only the right pedipalp is separated. It seems possible that this is the palp illustrated (which is also illustrated here), and that the drawing was later mirrored for publication. In one of the male 
<typeStatus box="[1334,1436,260,284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="99">paratypes</typeStatus>
the right pedipalp is separated as well, while the other specimen is intact. In the male from 
<collectingRegion box="[1159,1219,296,320]" country="Malta" name="Zebbug" pageId="2" pageNumber="99">Gozo</collectingRegion>
, the left pedipalp is separated, but its RTA is slightly damaged and both legs III are missing. The possibly subadult female (mentioned as “inadult” by Kritscher), stored together with the male 
<typeStatus box="[727,832,368,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="99">paratypes</typeStatus>
, does not have a scutum, but a paler cardiac mark. In the original description, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kritscher, E." box="[371,548,403,427]" pageId="2" pageNumber="99" pagination="117 - 156" refId="ref1703" refString="Kritscher, E. (1996) Ein Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Spinnen-Fauna der Maltesischen Inseln (Chelicerata: Araneae). Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, Serie B, 98, 117 - 156" type="journal article" year="1996">Kritscher (1996)</bibRefCitation>
also described the dorsal extension of the bifid RTA as being half as long as the part that points towards the bulbus. (“ […] 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="99">wobei der Fortsatz, der dem Palpentarsus aufliegt, spitz zuläuft und nur halb so lang ist wie jener Apophysenteil, der zum Bulbus zeigt</emphasis>
”). As shown in 
<figureCitation box="[889,954,475,500]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1970,1994]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,307,1946]" captionTargetId="figure-95@1.[151,1436,307,1946]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Poecilochroa loricata Kritscher, 1996, male holotype. a) habitus dorsal and separated leg I retrolateral, b) habitus ventral, c) right pedipalp retrolateral, d) right pedipalp ventral, e) retrolateral tibialapophysis, retrolateral-dorsal" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911141" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911141/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="99">Figs 1</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[1004,1019,476,500]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1946,1970]" captionTargetBox="[158,1417,641,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-279@2.[151,1436,632,1922]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Poecilochroa loricata Kritscher, 1996, male holotype, right pedipalpus, drawing (setae omitted). a) ventral, scale bar = 0.5 mm b) retrolateral, scale bar = 0.5 mm c) retrolateral tibial apophysis from retrolateral—dorsal. RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis, E = embolus, CD = conductor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911143" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911143/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="99">2</figureCitation>
, this only appears so when the pedipalp is shown in retrolateral view. Shown from a retrolateral-dorsal angle, it becomes clear that both extensions of the RTA are of similar length and shape. In addition, some of the taken measurements differ slightly from those given by Kritscher, e.g. the length of Pr of the 
<typeStatus box="[436,533,583,607]" pageId="2" pageNumber="99">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911143" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6911143" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911143/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="99" startId="2.[151,250,1946,1970]" targetBox="[158,1417,641,1907]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1946,2042]" pageId="2" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1946,1970]" pageId="2" pageNumber="99">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Kritscher, 1996" authorityName="Kritscher" authorityYear="1996" box="[283,672,1946,1970]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Poecilochroa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loricata">
<emphasis box="[283,505,1946,1970]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="99">Poecilochroa loricata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kritscher, E." box="[513,672,1946,1970]" pageId="2" pageNumber="99" pagination="117 - 156" refId="ref1703" refString="Kritscher, E. (1996) Ein Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Spinnen-Fauna der Maltesischen Inseln (Chelicerata: Araneae). Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, Serie B, 98, 117 - 156" type="journal article" year="1996">Kritscher, 1996</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, male holotype, right pedipalpus, drawing (setae omitted). a) ventral, scale bar = 0.5 mm b) retrolateral, scale bar = 0.5 mm c) retrolateral tibial apophysis from retrolateral—dorsal. RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis, E = embolus, CD = conductor.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1442,151,535]" pageId="3" pageNumber="100">
<bibRefCitation author="Wunderlich, J." box="[199,401,151,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="100" pagination="1 - 640" refId="ref1778" refString="Wunderlich, J. (2011) Extant and fossil spiders (Araneae). Beitrage zur Araneologie, 6, 1 - 640." type="journal article" year="2011">Wunderlich (2011)</bibRefCitation>
provisionally erected the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2011" box="[747,906,151,175]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Macarophaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[747,906,151,175]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="100">Macarophaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for three species formerly treated in 
<taxonomicName authority="Simon, 1893" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1893" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Scotophaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1301,1442,151,175]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="100">Scotophaeus</emphasis>
Simon, 1893
</taxonomicName>
and endemic to the Macaronesian Islands. While the validity of the genus and the generic placement of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kritscher" authorityYear="1996" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Poecilochroa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loricata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="100">P. loricata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is outside the scope of this note and should be addressed in a genus-wide revision including genetic analyses, it can be stated that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kritscher" authorityYear="1996" box="[342,452,259,283]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Poecilochroa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loricata">
<emphasis box="[342,452,259,283]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="100">P. loricata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares several characteristics of this genus: a uniform coloration, a membraneous conductor that entwines the embolus and the absence of a median bulbus apophysis.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1442,151,535]" pageId="3" pageNumber="100">
<materialsCitation country="Serbia" location="Asselar" pageId="3" pageNumber="100" specimenCount="1">
A possible synonymy with the similar 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fage" authorityYear="1929" box="[617,860,331,355]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Poecilochroa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antineae">
<emphasis box="[617,860,331,355]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="100">Poecilochroa antineae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, collected at the former military post 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B53224FFBAFFB88BC5FF36FC23FDD5:8EC3D5E9FFB9FFB88FA7FB6BFAC3FEA1" box="[1269,1349,331,355]" country="Serbia" name="Asselar" pageId="3" pageNumber="100">Asselar</location>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1386,1436,331,355]" name="Serbia" pageId="3" pageNumber="100">Mali</collectingCountry>
(formerly 
<collectingCountry box="[260,411,367,391]" name="Serbia" pageId="3" pageNumber="100">French Sudan</collectingCountry>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Fage, L." box="[422,538,368,392]" pageId="3" pageNumber="100" pagination="248 - 254" refId="ref1636" refString="Fage, L. (1929) Mission saharienne Augieras-Draper 1927 - 1928. Araignees nouvelles. Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris, (2) 1, 248 - 254." type="journal article" year="1929">Fage 1929</bibRefCitation>
), would extend the known distribution of the species into the more southern regions of the Sahara. However, only a re-examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[724,770,404,428]" pageId="3" pageNumber="100">type</typeStatus>
material would allow such an assessment
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
